sh, fish, pwsh).\n  \u001b[36mvibe\u001b[0m         Animated bear + tip rotation; ambient framework reference.\n\n\u001b[1mGLOBAL FLAGS\u001b[0m\n  \u001b[33m    --forcecolor\u001b[0m            Forces ANSI color emission even when output is not a TTY. Useful for piping into less -R or capturing colored logs to a ...\n  \u001b[33m    --noanimate\u001b[0m             Disables all animations even on a TTY\n  \u001b[33m    --nobanner\u001b[0m              Suppresses the banner on --help\n  \u001b[33m    --nocolor\u001b[0m               Disables ANSI color output. Equivalent to setting NO_COLOR in the environment\n  \u001b[33m    --otelendpoint \u003cvalue\u003e\u001b[0m  Overrides OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT for this invocation \u001b[2m[env: OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT]\u001b[0m\n  \u001b[33m    --profile \u003cvalue\u003e\u001b[0m       Writes pprof files to \u003cProfile\u003e.cpu/.heap/.goroutine\n  \u001b[33m-q, --quiet\u001b[0m                 Lowers log level to Warn; suppresses animations; keeps final summary\n  \u001b[33m-V, --verbose\u001b[0m               Raises log level to Debug\n  \u001b[33m    --veryverbose\u001b[0m           Raises log level to Trace level (custom)\n\nRun \u001b[36mglacier\u001b[0m \u003ccommand\u003e --help for command-specific help.\nRun \u001b[4mglacier explain\u001b[0m \u003ctopic\u003e for marker, exit-code, or config-key reference.\n"]
